  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "System Analyst",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Job responsibilities:</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Managing the client's Electronic Payment System (MEPS+) and domestic securities management systems in the company, and the MEPS+ Offline Contingency System (OCM+). </li>\n  <li>Supporting interbank payments in MEPS+ as well as company and government securities and trade settlements. </li>\n  <li>Understand and support the linkages between these systems and other market infrastructures such as the Automated Clearing House (ACH), FAST, and Singapore Exchange.</li>\n  <li>Manage the vendor and facilitate the delivery of on-going enhancements and regular system patching and testing. </li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<h2>Skillsets Required:</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Good Degree with at least 5 years' relevant experience in supporting and/or implementing payments and securities settlement systems.</li>\n  <li>Candidate must possess strong project and vendor management skills and proven ability in project delivery. Strong technical skills in developing Securities systems and understanding of instruments will be an added advantage.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience in managing operations, handling of issues, and ability to work with details and time-sensitive issues.</li>\n  <li>Strong written and communication skills will be an added advantage.</li>\n  <li>Strong technical knowledge of SWIFT messaging platform.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in code development of Java language, SQL, design, and architectural patterns.</li>\n  <li>Good working knowledge of Oracle Database, Microsoft SQL Server and fault-tolerant infrastructure concepts.</li>\n  <li>Good decision-making skills and response to high-pressure situations.</li>\n  <li>Experience using and configuring continuous integration tools and DevOps.</li>\n  <li>Able to collaborate and work effectively with multiple teams with varying skillsets.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Technologies Used</h2>\n<p>MEPS+</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>AIX for core system (primarily IBM suite of products)</li>\n  <li>Linux and Windows for non-core systems</li>\n  <li> Java</li>\n  <li>Oracle</li>\n  <li>SWIFT Alliance product suite</li>\n</ul>",
